folder: Tysen's Lane & Mill Road, Staten Island, NY
text:
(1)

Tysens Lane, west side, 550 feet north of Mill Road, showing the Lake-Tysen House. It dates in its origin to the late seventeenth or early eighteenth centuries. It is a fine example of Dutch Colonial architecture.

P. L. Sperr                          May 23, 1925

(2)

A distant view of the house and adjoining barns, seen from Mill Road.

P. L. Sperr                          May 23, 1925
